Articles.Content:
Just tried out New Horizons with the latest Kopernicus release. After patching kerbin.cfg, my somewhat limited testing indicates that everything is working as expected!

Although I'd recommend waiting for the official New Horizons patch, if anyone wants to manually patch and test a bit more, you can replace the contents of your kerbing.cfg in the New Horizons folder with the following:

    @Kopernicus:NEEDS[!GalacticNeighborhood]:AFTER[Kopernicus]
    {
        @Body[Kerbin]
        {
            @Properties
            {
                sphereOfInfluence = 6000000
                initialRotation = 55
            }
            @Orbit
            {
                semiMajorAxis = 5.4302e+7
                inclination = 0
                eccentricity = 0
                longitudeOfAscendingNode = 0
                meanAnomalyAtEpoch = 0
                epoch = 0
            }
            PostSpawnOrbit
            {
                referenceBody = Sonnah
            }
        }
    }

I think the other planets/moons do not need to be patched. I only tried the Mun, but patching it in a similar manner resulted in being unable to enter its <abbr title="Sphere of Influence">SOI</abbr> (not sure if that is intended behavior). I haven't tested with bodies other than Kerbin/Mun (and Sonnah, to the extent needed to get from Kerbin to Mun).
